        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <date>Wednesday, April 7</date>
                    <salute>Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I send you a fair copy of the Memorial.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> We have made another copy, so that I am ready to proceed, but I think I shall do nothing more until I hear from Paget<ref target="#foot.f3"/> &amp; have again seen you.</p>
<p>I will, if you will allow me call tomorrow morning.</p>
<p>Very truly yours | J Burdon Sanderson</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to the memorial (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had worked with <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> to draft a petition to regulate vivisection (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9875.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Huxley, [4 April 1875]</ref> and n. 2).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3643.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">James Paget</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
